Title
Expense Tracker System using Python
________________________________________
1. Introduction
The Expense Tracker is a Python-based application designed to help users record and manage daily expenses. It allows continuous input of expenses and calculates the total expenditure using real-time processing.
________________________________________
2. Objectives
•	To track daily expenses efficiently 
•	To implement accumulator logic 
•	To understand loops and input handling 
•	To apply IPO (Input-Process-Output) model 
________________________________________
3. Technologies Used
•	Python 
•	Command Line Interface (CLI) 
________________________________________
4. Features
•	Add multiple expenses 
•	Continuous data entry 
•	Calculate total spending 
•	Exit option for user 
________________________________________
5. Methodology (IPO Model)
Input:
•	User enters expense amount 
Process:
•	Expense is added to total using accumulator 
Output:
•	Displays updated total expense 
________________________________________
6. Code Explanation
•	A variable total is used to store accumulated expenses 
•	A while loop is used for continuous input 
•	Input is converted into numeric form (float) 
•	Condition is used to exit program 
__________________________
8. Conclusion
This project helped in understanding real-time data processing and accumulator patterns in Python.

